history.content: You might want to drop and add to the discussion that has the most open seats. You can't get enrolled into a discussion but not the corresponding lecture, vice versa. Only discussion waitlist matters, at least for CS170 that's how they move the waitlist. In 189, I believe you can attend any discussion, not necessarily the one that you are registered for.

children.subject: Attendance policies do not affect enrollment policies, no.
For 188, you can also attend any discussion. Does this change how the waitlist is processed???

history.content:
Hi, I feel like the staff has answered this many times so please review similar questions from the last few weeks about dropping yourself.

No, students may not "get into" or enroll in a course if they're waitlisted. This has never been possible.

I am currently pretty high on the waitlist for cs188 but also wailisted for a discussion that is full. For this class, there are more discussion section seats available than lecture seats and so I am a little afraid of not getting into the class due to being waitlisted in a full discussion while open discussions are available. To my knowledge, there is no means to swap discussion sections while waitlisted. 

I am wondering what the best course of action is to get enrolled? Is it possible to get into the class while still waitlisted for a discussion?
history.subject: Waitlist processing unable to change discussion sections
